The paper deals with image classification using deep convolutional neural networks and complementary parts models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as weakly supervised learning and LSTM networks, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of object detection and instance segmentation, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with image processing and feature extraction, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) respectively.
